If there are any additional discrete elements on the M2 line (like capacitors/resistors/diodes), they might be used to detect resetting the console, because when the RESET button is held, the M2 line is tied high for a long amount, so the capacitor might be charged/discharged.<br /><br />A lot of pirate XXX-in-1 games uses this to detect the reset of console.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4898">krzysiobal</a> — Sun Dec 28, 2014 7:07 pm</p><hr />
