<div class="quotetitle">guitarzombie wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />no it was def a resistor, color codes and all. Couldnt read the bands so i measured it amd got 182 Ohms.<br /></div><br />It's most definitely a capacitor, if you look closely at the symbol underneath that component, you'll notice that it's the symbol for a non-polarized capacitor and not a resistor. Some axial ceramic capacitors will have colored bands that represent its value, much like a resistor does. You'll also notice that the cap is also connected between 5V and ground, which shows that it's a bypass cap.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5671">ApolloBoy</a> — Mon Nov 24, 2014 4:40 pm</p><hr />
